      {
        "title": "tests/test_agent.py",
        "content": "from freezegun import freeze_time\nfrom agent import _normalize_ats, cmd_db_mark\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_replaces_smart_quotes_in_text(self):\n        html = \"<p>\\u201cHello\\u201d</p>\"\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert '\"Hello\"' in out\n        assert counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_style_or_script_blocks(self):\n        html = \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>\\u2014</p>\"\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in out.split(\"</style>\")[0]   # left alone in <style>\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1                  # only the <p> one counted\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_tag_attributes(self):\n        html = '<a href=\"x\\u2014y\">text\\u2014here</a>'\n        out, _ = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert 'href=\"x\\u2014y\"' in out\n        assert \"text-here\" in out\n\n\nclass TestDbMark:\n    def test_invalid_watermark_returns_exit_code_2(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n        code = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])\n        assert code == 2\n\n    def test_neither_watermark_nor_now_returns_exit_code_2(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 2\n\n    @freeze_time(\"2026-07-16T12:00:00Z\")\n    def test_now_flag_sets_current_iso_time(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\n\")\n        assert cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(cfg)]) == 0\n```\n\n**`cmd_db_new` gaps** (needs a `Store` fixture pre-seeded with rows across multiple `first_seen` timestamps):\n- first run (no marker) uses `since_days` window, not the marker\n- `--posted-days` combined with `--dated-only`: undated rows kept vs dropped\n- truncation happens only at `first_seen` group boundaries — a test asserting a limit of 5 with a 6-row group at the boundary keeps all 6 (not chopped mid-group) and reports `truncated=True`\n- `watermark` returned equals the last *fully included* group's timestamp, not the last row's\n\n**Untested entirely:** `_chrome_bin` (env var priority vs `PATH` vs hardcoded macOS paths vs `sys.exit`), `cmd_pdf_render` (missing input file → exit 2; temp file cleanup on subprocess failure — use `finally` + mocked `subprocess.run`; non-`%PDF` output → exit 1), `cmd_report_num`, `main()`'s argv dispatch/flag-splitting logic, `run_claude`/`_claude` (subprocess/`os.execvp` — needs mocking, not real execution).\n\n---\n\n",
